"From the beginning, IBM has been more of an institution than a technology company", says economist Rosabeth Moss Kanter, professor at Harvard Business School and author of the book on IBM.
"IBM is not a technology company, but a company that tries to solve business problems for technology users", says George Colony of Forrester Research.
As the company itself says, there is a difference between going into business and directly creating a business.
