The building was adequate but lacked the space and technology to make a museum; no wall to hang art, no good atmosphere.
Despite this it was used until contemporary art in Vienna had a new home.
The building has been vacant since 2001 and is decaying.
Currently, architect Adolf Krischanitz has refurbished the pavilion, now calling it "house 21" and will be used in the future as a contemporary art museum.
