He knew the project and the problem of the building, which disappeared with its transfer to Vienna in its change of use with generosity and ease.
In the current reforms there are big problems, the building was "an energy devourer", Krischanitz said.
The windows of the glass façade were changed, an insulating glass reinforced with glass fibre was installed and the glass roof was replaced by a special safety glass.
Thermal bridges and steel beams were reinforced or replaced and asbestos roofs were rehabilitated.
Two basements were used for the new use, a light panel lowered between the house and the street provides illumination, a bridge serves to enter the almost new building, but still the Schwanzer Pavilion.
